	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002088_0001"><!--pb/@n='21r'--></pb>
<lb/><p rend="center"><date when="1864-10-13">13<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Oct<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>October</expan></choice> 1864</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My dear <persName>Waller</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Read the enclosed
<lb/>and you will be able
<lb/>to form an opinion
<lb/>on the accounts sent
<lb/>to me. the <term type="animal">mules</term> and
<lb/>one cart are ￡144.!
<lb/>shipping them to
<lb/><placeName><region>Natal</region></placeName> &amp; <placeName><region>Zambesi</region></placeName>
<lb/>￡21. &amp; ￡25 - Keep 
<lb/>at <placeName><region>Natal</region></placeName> ￡10 - though
<lb/>I gave <persName>Sir George
<lb/>Grey</persName> power to send</p>

<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/><!-- this vertical text follows on from the end of p4 and then continues to the left margin of p2 AM -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">shooting experience - no end of <term type="animal">rabbits</term> - 
<lb/><term type="animal">partridges</term> - <term type="animal">pheasants</term> - <term type="animal">hares</term> here but <choice><sic>its</sic><corr>it's</corr></choice></p>
     
<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/><!-- this text is not quite vertical or horizontal - in fact it is written diagonally from top left to bottom right across top quarter of page AM -->
<lb/><ab rend="no-indent">could it be sent with a
<lb/>remark from you</ab>


	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002088_0002"><!--pb/@n='84v'--></pb>
<lb/><p>the <orgName>mission party</orgName> &amp;
<lb/>goods by the Hetty Ellen <!-- Unsure if this is a personal name, or name of a ship?? HB 1/16/12 --><!-- It's a ship AM -->
<lb/>when she came to the
<lb/><placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName> - I had to pay
<lb/>￡354 - 7 - 6 by an
<lb/>agreement made by
<lb/><persName>Captain Wilson</persName> &amp; <persName>Rae</persName>
<lb/>at <placeName><country><choice><orig>Mosambique</orig><reg>Mozambique</reg></choice></country></placeName> for
<lb/>additional freight - 
<lb/>and I thought half of
<lb/>this might be paid
<lb/>by the <orgName>mission</orgName> but
<lb/>knowing that I had
<lb/>￡50 for <term type="animal">mules</term> to pay
<lb/>I did not send any
<lb/>account to the
<lb/><placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName> - the goods</p>

<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/><!-- this vertical text follows on from the end of p1 and then continues to the left margin of p3 AM -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">beastly to shoot when one has leave nay is
<lb/>even - invited to shoot. The pleasure of</p>

<!-- Vertical text in the right margin belongs to the next page, so text will be transcribed there HB 10/2/12 -->


	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002088_0003"><!--pb/@n='85r'--></pb>
<lb/><p>given by <persName>Bishop
<lb/>Tozer</persName> might square
<lb/>the matter but I wish
<lb/>to deal fairly &amp;
<lb/>in a friendly way
<lb/>I think put it
<lb/>to themselves - but
<lb/>though saying "quits"
<lb/>would be the easier
<lb/>way. and. I guess
<lb/>it might be best
<lb/>for the <orgName>mission</orgName>
<lb/>I <choice><sic>dont</sic><corr>don't</corr></choice> know <orgName>my
<lb/>men</orgName>. I would prefer
<lb/>that they had the
<lb/>best of it for in my
<lb/>heart of hearts I wished
<lb/>them success</p>

<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/><!-- this vertical text follows on from the end of p2 AM -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">sinning is <unclear cert="low">awanting</unclear> Thanks for the Photos.
<lb/>had you been of <orgName>my party</orgName> I should have tried
<lb/>to get a <orgName>consulate</orgName> for you. <persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002088_0004"><!--pb/@n='85v'--></pb>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">After reading &amp; you
<lb/>think it might send
<lb/>the enclosed on - I see
<lb/><persName>Steere</persName> puts in a note
<lb/>that the bales of calico
<lb/>for which I gave
<lb/>double what he sold
<lb/>others at <placeName><settlement type="town">Senna</settlement></placeName> are 
<lb/>very much below their
<lb/>real value - You may
<lb/>do me a good turn
<lb/>if you help them with
<lb/>your views as to what
<lb/>is right. I never intended
<lb/>to take anything but the
<lb/>bills sent set up my
<lb/>back. Thanks for the
<lb/>note for the other affair
<lb/>I wrote a note last
<lb/>night with my <term type="animal">Rabbit</term></p><!-- see continuation from here - vertical text in left margin of p1 AM -->
			
</div>
